Conduct a thorough review of the existing cloud infrastructure and identify areas that require modernization or improvement.
Develop a cloud migration strategy to move existing applications and data to modern, secure, and interoperable cloud infrastructure.
Implement a data governance framework to ensure that data is managed effectively across the organization.
Develop and maintain an enterprise data architecture that supports data integration and interoperability across different systems.
Ensure that the cloud infrastructure is compliant with relevant security and privacy standards, such as the Personal Information Protection and Electronic Documents Act (PIPEDA) and the Canadian Digital Privacy Act.

Develop and implement technology governance policies and procedures that align with industry best practices and support the organization's strategic objectives.
Engage with stakeholders across the organization to understand their technology needs and ensure that technology solutions are aligned with business requirements.
Develop a roadmap for the implementation of new technology solutions, taking into account budgetary constraints, resource availability, and organizational priorities.
Establish a governance board to oversee technology initiatives and ensure that they align with the organization's strategic goals.
Provide training and support to staff to ensure that they have the skills and knowledge required to effectively use technology solutions.

Provides modern, secure, and interoperable cloud infrastructure for public health intelligence, data systems, and enterprise data.
Manages the collection, storage, analysis, and dissemination of data through cloud-based technologies.
Ensures that data is accessible, reliable, and of high quality to support evidence-based decision making in public health.
Provides ongoing support and maintenance of cloud infrastructure to ensure that it remains secure, stable, and compliant with relevant standards and regulations.

Manages the enterprise architecture to ensure that it aligns with the organization's strategic objectives and supports efficient and effective business operations.
Develops and implements technology governance policies and procedures that align with industry best practices and support the organization's strategic goals.
Ensures that technology solutions are implemented and managed in a way that is compliant with relevant security and privacy standards, such as the Personal Information Protection and Electronic Documents Act (PIPEDA) and the Canadian Digital Privacy Act.
Provides ongoing support and maintenance of IT systems, assets, and infrastructure to ensure that they remain secure, reliable, and available to support the organization's business operations.

Develops and implements policies and procedures that govern the use of technology across the organization, including risk management, compliance management, and performance measurement and reporting.
Provides oversight and guidance on the use of technology to ensure that it aligns with the organization's strategic goals and objectives, and that it is compliant with relevant regulations and standards.
Ensures that the organization's technology assets and infrastructure are managed and maintained in a way that is secure, reliable, and available to support the organization's business operations.
Monitors and evaluates the performance of technology solutions and services to identify areas for improvement and to ensure that they are delivering value to the organization.

Develops and manages strategic partnerships and collaborations with internal and external stakeholders to support the organization's goals and objectives.
Identifies potential partners and evaluates their strategic alignment with the organization's goals and objectives.
Negotiates and manages partnership agreements to ensure that they are mutually beneficial and aligned with the organization's goals and objectives.
Monitors and evaluates the performance of partnerships to ensure that they are meeting their goals and objectives, and identifies areas for improvement to ensure that partnerships continue to deliver value to the organization.
Manages the deployment, maintenance, and optimization of cloud-based technologies to support the organization's data management and analytics needs.
Ensures that data and applications are integrated and interoperable across different systems, platforms, and technologies to support effective data management and analysis in the organization.
Manages and supports the deployment, maintenance, and optimization of applications to support the organization's data management and analytics needs.
Manages the collection, storage, organization, and retrieval of data to support the organization's data management and analytics needs.
Analyzes and reports on data to support evidence-based decision making in the organization and to provide insights that inform business operations and strategy.
Manages the organization's enterprise architecture to ensure that it aligns with the organization's strategic goals and supports efficient and effective business operations.

Manages the delivery and support of IT services to ensure that they meet the organization's business needs and are delivered in a way that is secure, reliable, and compliant with relevant standards and regulations.

Manages the organization's cloud-based IT assets, including infrastructure, platforms, and software, to ensure that they are acquired, deployed, and maintained in a way that supports the organization's business operations and goals.

Manages the security and privacy practices and policies for cloud-based data and systems to ensure that data is protected from unauthorized access, use, disclosure, disruption, modification, or destruction, and that cloud-based systems are compliant with relevant security and privacy regulations and standards.
Develops and manages solution architectures that align with the organization's strategic goals and support efficient and effective business operations, with a focus on cloud-based solutions.

Establishes and manages the policies, processes, and procedures for cloud-based IT governance to ensure that the organization's technology investments and activities align with its strategic goals and are compliant with relevant regulations and standards.
Develops and manages cloud-based technology policies to guide the organization's technology investments and activities, and to ensure that they are compliant with relevant regulations and standards.

Identifies, assesses, and manages cloud-based technology risks to ensure that the organization's technology investments and activities are aligned with its strategic goals and are compliant with relevant regulations and standards.

Manages and monitors cloud-based technology compliance with relevant regulations and standards to ensure that the organization's technology investments and activities are aligned with its strategic goals and meet legal and regulatory requirements.

Measures and reports on the performance of cloud-based technology solutions and services to ensure that they are meeting the organization's business needs and delivering value, and to identify areas for improvement.

"Strategic Alliances is like building a network of fertile soil on a barren planet. By cultivating relationships and partnerships, we can create a rich ecosystem that supports growth and innovation, and transforms the landscape of the organization."
Just as fertile soil provides the necessary nutrients for plants to grow, strategic alliances provide the necessary resources and support for the organization to achieve its goals and objectives.

Identifies and selects potential partners and collaborators for strategic alliances, based on their alignment with the organization's goals and objectives, and their ability to provide the necessary resources and support.
Manages ongoing communication and relationships with partners and collaborators to ensure that the strategic alliances remain effective and aligned with the organization's goals and objectives.

Develops and manages a network of strategic partnerships and collaborations that support the organization's goals and objectives, and identifies opportunities to expand and strengthen the partnership ecosystem.

Negotiates and manages partnership agreements with internal and external partners to establish the terms and conditions of the strategic alliance, and to ensure that the partnership is mutually beneficial and aligned with the organization's goals and objectives.

Monitors and evaluates the performance of strategic alliances to ensure that they are meeting their goals and objectives, and identifies opportunities for improvement and optimization to enhance the value and impact of the partnerships.
A Business Function represents a collection of business behavior based on a chosen set of criteria (typically required business resources and/or competencies), closely aligned to an organization

A Business Service exposes the functionality of Business Roles or Collaborations to their environment. This functionality is accessed through one or more business interfaces. A Business Service is realized by one or more Business Processes, Business Functions.
A Driver represents an external or internal condition that motivates an organization to define its goals and implement the changes necessary to achieve them.
A Capability focuses on business outcomes. It provides a high-level view of the current and desired abilities of an organization
A Goal represents a high-level statement of intent, direction, or desired end state for an organization and its stakeholders
